@using FREAK_Dev.Components
@inject IJSRuntime JSRuntime
<PageTitle>FREAK - Home</PageTitle>
<h2>Q / A</h2>
<label class="title">Q: Why FREAK?</label>
<div class="container dark">
    <label class="title">A:</label>
    <p>
        FREAK is meant to be as fast as Rust, with memory safety features. FREAK is designed for weebs. FREAK is designed for people who want to write code that looks like it came out of a visual novel. FREAK is designed for people who want to write code that only makes sense at 3am. FREAK is designed for people who want to write code that compiles to native binaries. FREAK is designed for people who want to write code that has a borrow checker that yells at you in character. FREAK is designed for people who want to write code that has mood types. FREAK is designed for people who want to write code that has a package manager called Hangar. FREAK is designed for people who want to write code that has a UI framework called freak-ui. FREAK is designed for people who want to write code where every variable is called pilot because you are always on a mission.
    </p>
</div>

<label class="title">Q: What is FREAK?</label>
<div class="container dark">
    <label class="title">A:</label>
    <p>
        FREAK is a compiled, statically-typed, memory-safe systems language with a syntax inspired by visual novels, anime, and the kind of programming that only makes sense at 3am.

        It compiles to native binaries. It has a borrow checker. It has mood types. It has a package manager called Hangar. It has a UI framework called freak-ui. And every variable is called pilot because you are always on a mission.
    </p>
</div>
