<label class="title">01- Syntax</label>
<h1 >
    Write code like
    you mean it.
</h1>
<h3>Variables are <strong>pilot</strong>. Functions are <strong>task</strong>. Errors propagate with <strong>? </strong>.<i> And yes, the anime operators are real and they compile.</i></h3>
<div>
    <div style="background-color: #040414; height: 10rem; font-family: Pixel Cyr Normal;">
        <div style="height: 2.5rem;  " ></div>
        <p>
        <span style="color: rgb(255, 107, 168);">pilot</span> name = <span style="color: rgb(255, 204, 102);">"Shirogane Takeru"</span> <br />
        <span style="color: rgb(255, 107, 168);">pilot</span> power = <span style="color: rgb(255, 153, 102);">9001</span><br />
        <span style="color: rgb(255, 107, 168);">pilot</span> active = <span style="color: rgb(255, 107, 168);">true</span>
        </p>
       
        </div>
    <label>Freak can assume the type of a variable, without the need to declare it. <br /> If you wish to, you can also declare the type.</label>
    <div style="background-color: #040414; height: 10rem; font-family: Pixel Cyr Normal;">
    <div style="height: 2.5rem;  "></div>
    <p>
        <span style="color: rgb(255, 107, 168);">pilot</span> name: <span style="color: rgb(0, 229, 204);">word</span> = <span style="color: rgb(255, 204, 102);">"Shirogane Takeru"</span> <br />
        <span style="color: rgb(255, 107, 168);">pilot</span> power: <span style="color: rgb(0, 229, 204);">int</span> = <span style="color: rgb(255, 153, 102);">9001</span><br />
        <span style="color: rgb(255, 107, 168);">pilot</span> active: <span style="color: rgb(0, 229, 204);">bool</span> = <span style="color: rgb(255, 107, 168);">true</span>
    </p>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<label class="title">02- Features</label>
<h1>
    Everything you <span style="color: #f0146e;">need.</span> <br />
    Nothing you don't.
</h1>
<div style="  display: grid;  grid-template-columns: auto auto auto;  padding: 0.5rem;">
    <div class="container">
        <div style="height: 1.5rem;"></div>
        <label class="title">01 - <span style="color: #f0146e;">ANIME</span> LOGIC LAYER</label>
        <div style="height: 0.5rem;"></div>
        <p>Death flag detection. Route types. Power level enforcement at compile time. PLUS ULTRA, NAKAMA, and TSUNDERE operators that compile to real C. It's not a joke. It compiles.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
        <div style="height: 1.5rem;"></div>
        <label class="title">02 - MEMORY <span style="color: #f0146e;">SAFETY</span></label>
        <div style="height: 0.5rem;"></div>
        <p>Ownership system with<span style="color: #f0146e;"> lend </span> and <span style="color: #f0146e;">lend mut</span>. No null — ever.<span style="color: #f0146e;"> maybe&lt;T&gt;</span> and <span style="color: #f0146e;">result &lt;T,E&gt;</span> everywhere. The borrow checker delivers errors in character voice.</p>
    </div>
        <div class="container">
        <div style="height: 1.5rem;"></div>
        <label class="title">03 - SQUADRON <span style="color: #f0146e;">CONCURRENCY</span></label>
        <div style="height: 0.5rem;"></div>
        <p>Threads are sorties. Channels are comms. Mutexes are briefing rooms. The XM3 concurrency model races parallel branches and commits the fastest valid result.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
        <div style="height: 1.5rem;"></div>
        <label class="title">04 - REAL <span style="color: #f0146e;">GENERICS</span></label>
        <div style="height: 0.5rem;"></div>
        <p>Full <span style="color: #f0146e;">&lt;T&gt;</span> generic types with <span style="color: #f0146e;">doctrine</span> trait bounds. Shapes, tasks, impl blocks — all generic. Zero runtime overhead through monomorphisation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
        <div style="height: 1.5rem;"></div>
        <label class="title">05 - HANGAR <span style="color: #f0146e;">PACKAGES</span></label>
        <div style="height: 0.5rem;"></div>
        <p>The package manager is called Hangar because you're storing deployable units.<span style="color: #f0146e;"> freak hangar install</span>. <span style="color: #f0146e;">freak hangar launch</span>. The theming is not optional. It is doctrine.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
        <div style="height: 1.5rem;"></div>
        <label class="title">06 - NARRATIVE <span style="color: #f0146e;">ERRORS</span></label>
        <div style="height: 0.5rem;"></div>
        <p>Type mismatches are delivered by Yuuko being sarcastic. Lifetime errors come from Meiya, formally disappointed. Unused foreshadowing is narrated by a tired Takeru who has seen this mistake four times across timelines.</p>
    </div>
</div>
<hr /> 
<label class="title">03- Installation</label>
<h1>
    One click.
  <span style="color: #f0146e;"> It's yours. </span>
</h1>
<div class="container light">
    <label class="title">Install</label>
    <p>irm https://raw.githubusercontent.com/FREAK-lang-dev/Freak-lang/main/install.ps1 | iex</p>
</div>
<div class="container light">
    <label class="title">Install</label>
    <p>freakc hangar init MyProject</p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">
    <button @onclick="Copy1" type="button" class="btn">Copy installation command</button>
    <button @onclick="Copy2" type="button" class="btn">Copy initialization command</button>
</div>
